                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 367.11/12.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Ambassador</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams.—Paraphrases.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Constantinople</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-11-07">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 7, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The measures I was taking when I sent my telegram of November 5, 2 p.m., have
                    been substantially carried out and appear adequate, in conjunction with further
                    possibility of refuge on British vessels here in case of need which my British
                    colleague informs me can be given. Highly improbable duration of situation as
                    long as a month. Six neutral vessels will arrive to-morrow; more later. City
                    quiet. Unnecessary to announce intended despatch of an American war vessel.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Rockhill</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
